content:
Clean and Prepare Data Intelligently with Column Profiles and Smart Suggestions

The column profile gives you key insights into the quality of your data and suggests additional transformations to help you clean and prepare it. This profile is especially useful when you are combining data from different sources, where inconsistencies are often introduced.

To open the column profile in a Data Prep recipe, click  or select Show Profile from the column's menu.

The sections that you see in the column profile depend on the type of column:

Sample Size: The number of rows used to generate the column profile data.
Valid Values: An idea of how the column is populated. A high proportion of null values can indicate lower quality data.
Frequent Values: The count for each of the top five values in the column.
String Length (Dimension Columns Only): A breakdown of the number of characters in dimension values.
Clusters (Dimension Columns Only): Groupings of similar values presented as a stacked bar.
Anomalies (Dimension Columns Only): Values that are not consistent with other values in the column.
Histogram (Measure and Date Columns Only): The distribution of values in a measure or date column.

For dimension and date columns, click one or more bars to see suggested transformations for those values in the Suggestions bar. CRM Analytics suggests Bucket By Cluster transformation when it identifies clusters, and Anomalies transformation when it finds inconsistent values.

To help with your data cleansing, CRM Analytics also provides suggestions based on the profile results.
title: Clean and Prepare Data with Column Profiles
